events.description: A Latin Christian fleet defeats a larger Turkish fleet in the battle of Pallene during the Smyrniote crusades.
events.html: • 1344 – A Latin Christian fleet defeats a larger Turkish fleet in the battle of Pallene during the Smyrniote crusades.[1]

events.description: Julian of Norwich has visions of Jesus while suffering from a life-threatening illness, visions which are later described and interpreted in her book Revelations of Divine Love.
events.html: • 1373 – Julian of Norwich has visions of Jesus while suffering from a life-threatening illness, visions which are later described and interpreted in her book Revelations of Divine Love.[2]

events.description: Amerigo Vespucci, this time under Portuguese flag, set sail for western lands.
events.html: • 1501 – Amerigo Vespucci, this time under Portuguese flag, set sail for western lands.[3]

events.description: Mary, Queen of Scots, is defeated at the Battle of Langside, part of the civil war between Queen Mary and the supporters of her son, James VI.
events.html: • 1568 – Mary, Queen of Scots, is defeated at the Battle of Langside, part of the civil war between Queen Mary and the supporters of her son, James VI.[4]

events.description: Sword duel between Miyamoto Musashi and Sasaki Kojiro on the shores of Ganryū Island. Kojiro dies at the end.
events.html: • 1612 – Sword duel between Miyamoto Musashi and Sasaki Kojiro on the shores of Ganryū Island. Kojiro dies at the end.[5][6]

events.description: Dutch statesman Johan van Oldenbarnevelt is executed in The Hague after being convicted of treason.
events.html: • 1619 – Dutch statesman Johan van Oldenbarnevelt is executed in The Hague after being convicted of treason.

events.description: A Venetian fleet under Admiral Cort Adeler breaks through a line of galleys and defeats the Turkish navy.
events.html: • 1654 – A Venetian fleet under Admiral Cort Adeler breaks through a line of galleys and defeats the Turkish navy.[7]

events.description: War of the Bavarian Succession: Russian and French mediators at the Congress of Teschen negotiate an end to the war. In the agreement Austria receives the part of its territory that was taken from it (the Innviertel).
events.html: • 1779 – War of the Bavarian Succession: Russian and French mediators at the Congress of Teschen negotiate an end to the war. In the agreement Austria receives the part of its territory that was taken from it (the Innviertel).

events.description: The Cumberland Compact is signed by leaders of the settlers in the Cumberland River area of what would become the U.S. state of Tennessee, providing for democratic government and a formal system of justice.
events.html: • 1780 – The Cumberland Compact is signed by leaders of the settlers in the Cumberland River area of what would become the U.S. state of Tennessee, providing for democratic government and a formal system of justice.[8]

events.description: Forces sent by Yusuf Karamanli of Tripoli to retake Derna from the Americans attack the city.
events.html: • 1804 – Forces sent by Yusuf Karamanli of Tripoli to retake Derna from the Americans attack the city.

events.description: Ecuador gains its independence from Gran Colombia.
events.html: • 1830 – Ecuador gains its independence from Gran Colombia.

events.description: Mexican–American War: The United States declares war on the Federal Republic of Mexico following a dispute over the American annexation of the Republic of Texas and a Mexican military incursion.
events.html: • 1846 – Mexican–American War: The United States declares war on the Federal Republic of Mexico following a dispute over the American annexation of the Republic of Texas and a Mexican military incursion.[9]

entities.name: United States declaration of war on Mexico

events.description: American Civil War: Queen Victoria of the United Kingdom issues a "proclamation of neutrality" which recognizes the Confederacy as having belligerent rights.
events.html: • 1861 – American Civil War: Queen Victoria of the United Kingdom issues a "proclamation of neutrality" which recognizes the Confederacy as having belligerent rights.

entities.name: United Kingdom and the American Civil War

events.description: The Great Comet of 1861 is discovered by John Tebbutt of Windsor, New South Wales, Australia.
events.html: • 1861 – The Great Comet of 1861 is discovered by John Tebbutt of Windsor, New South Wales, Australia.

events.description: Pakistan's (then a part of British India) first railway line  opens, from Karachi to Kotri.
events.html: • 1861 – Pakistan's (then a part of British India) first railway line opens, from Karachi to Kotri.

entities.name: History of rail transport in Pakistan

events.description: The USS Planter, a steamer and gunship, steals through Confederate lines and is passed to the Union, by a southern slave, Robert Smalls, who later was officially appointed as captain, becoming the first black man to command a United States ship.
events.html: • 1862 – The USS Planter, a steamer and gunship, steals through Confederate lines and is passed to the Union, by a southern slave, Robert Smalls, who later was officially appointed as captain, becoming the first black man to command a United States ship.

events.description: With the passage of the Lei Áurea ("Golden Law"), the Empire of Brazil abolishes slavery.
events.html: • 1888 – With the passage of the Lei Áurea ("Golden Law"), the Empire of Brazil abolishes slavery.

events.description: The first edition of the Giro d'Italia, a long-distance multiple-stage bicycle race, began in Milan; the Italian cyclist Luigi Ganna was the eventual winner.
events.html: • 1909 – The first edition of the Giro d'Italia, a long-distance multiple-stage bicycle race, began in Milan; the Italian cyclist Luigi Ganna was the eventual winner. [10]

events.description: The Royal Flying Corps, the forerunner of the Royal Air Force, is established in the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1912 – The Royal Flying Corps, the forerunner of the Royal Air Force, is established in the United Kingdom.

events.description: Three children report the first apparition of Our Lady of Fátima in Fátima, Portugal.
events.html: • 1917 – Three children report the first apparition of Our Lady of Fátima in Fátima, Portugal.

events.description: World War II: Germany's conquest of France begins, as the German army crosses the Meuse. Winston Churchill makes his "blood, toil, tears, and sweat" speech to the House of Commons.
events.html: • 1940 – World War II: Germany's conquest of France begins, as the German army crosses the Meuse. Winston Churchill makes his "blood, toil, tears, and sweat" speech to the House of Commons.

entities.name: House of Commons of the United Kingdom

events.description: World War II: Operations Vulcan and Strike force the surrender of the last Axis troops in Tunisia.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: Operations Vulcan and Strike force the surrender of the last Axis troops in Tunisia.

events.description: World War II: Yevgeny Khaldei's photograph Raising a Flag over the Reichstag is published in Ogonyok magazine.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Yevgeny Khaldei's photograph Raising a Flag over the Reichstag is published in Ogonyok magazine.[11]

entities.name: Raising a Flag over the Reichstag

events.description: Arab–Israeli War: The Kfar Etzion massacre occurs, a day prior to the Israeli Declaration of Independence.
events.html: • 1948 – Arab–Israeli War: The Kfar Etzion massacre occurs, a day prior to the Israeli Declaration of Independence.

events.description: The inaugural Formula One World Championship race takes place at Silverstone Circuit. The race was won by Giuseppe Farina, who would go on to become the inaugural champion that year.
events.html: • 1950 – The inaugural Formula One World Championship race takes place at Silverstone Circuit. The race was won by Giuseppe Farina, who would go on to become the inaugural champion that year.[12]

entities.name: List of Formula One World Drivers' Champions

events.description: The 400th anniversary of the founding of the National University of San Marcos is commemorated by the opening of the first large-capacity stadium in Peru.
events.html: • 1951 – The 400th anniversary of the founding of the National University of San Marcos is commemorated by the opening of the first large-capacity stadium in Peru.

events.description: The Rajya Sabha, the upper house of the Parliament of India, holds its first sitting.
events.html: • 1952 – The Rajya Sabha, the upper house of the Parliament of India, holds its first sitting.

events.description: The anti-National Service Riots, by Chinese middle school students in Singapore, take place.
events.html: • 1954 – The anti-National Service Riots, by Chinese middle school students in Singapore, take place.

events.description: During a visit to Caracas, Venezuela, the US Vice President Richard Nixon's car is attacked by anti-American demonstrators.
events.html: • 1958 – During a visit to Caracas, Venezuela, the US Vice President Richard Nixon's car is attacked by anti-American demonstrators.

events.description: May 1958 crisis: A group of French military officers lead a coup in Algiers demanding that a government of national unity be formed with Charles de Gaulle at its head in order to defend French control of Algeria.
events.html: • 1958 – May 1958 crisis: A group of French military officers lead a coup in Algiers demanding that a government of national unity be formed with Charles de Gaulle at its head in order to defend French control of Algeria.

events.description: Ben Carlin becomes the first (and only) person to circumnavigate the world by amphibious vehicle, having travelled over 17,000 kilometres (11,000 mi) by sea and 62,000 kilometres (39,000 mi) by land during a ten-year journey.
events.html: • 1958 – Ben Carlin becomes the first (and only) person to circumnavigate the world by amphibious vehicle, having travelled over 17,000 kilometres (11,000 mi) by sea and 62,000 kilometres (39,000 mi) by land during a ten-year journey.

events.description: Hundreds of University of California, Berkeley students congregate for the first day of protest against a visit by the House Committee on Un-American Activities.
events.html: • 1960 – Hundreds of University of California, Berkeley students congregate for the first day of protest against a visit by the House Committee on Un-American Activities.

events.description: Dr. Zakir Husain becomes the third President of India. He is the first Muslim President of the Indian Union. He holds this position until August 24, 1969.
events.html: • 1967 – Dr. Zakir Husain becomes the third President of India. He is the first Muslim President of the Indian Union. He holds this position until August 24, 1969.

events.description: In the aftermath of the 1969 Malaysian general election, Sino-Malay sectarian violence erupted in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
events.html: • 1969 – In the aftermath of the 1969 Malaysian general election, Sino-Malay sectarian violence erupted in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.[13]

events.description: A fire occurs in the Sennichi Department Store in Osaka, Japan. Blocked exits and non-functional elevators result in 118 fatalities (many victims leaping to their deaths).
events.html: • 1972 – A fire occurs in the Sennichi Department Store in Osaka, Japan. Blocked exits and non-functional elevators result in 118 fatalities (many victims leaping to their deaths).

events.description: The Troubles: A car bombing outside a crowded pub in Belfast sparks a two-day gun battle involving the Provisional IRA, Ulster Volunteer Force and British Army. Seven people are killed and over 66 injured.
events.html: • 1972 – The Troubles: A car bombing outside a crowded pub in Belfast sparks a two-day gun battle involving the Provisional IRA, Ulster Volunteer Force and British Army. Seven people are killed and over 66 injured.

events.description: An F3 tornado hits Kalamazoo County, Michigan. President Jimmy Carter declares it a federal disaster area.
events.html: • 1980 – An F3 tornado hits Kalamazoo County, Michigan. President Jimmy Carter declares it a federal disaster area.

events.description: Mehmet Ali Ağca attempts to assassinate Pope John Paul II in St. Peter's Square in Rome. The Pope is rushed to the Agostino Gemelli University Polyclinic to undergo emergency surgery and survives.
events.html: • 1981 – Mehmet Ali Ağca attempts to assassinate Pope John Paul II in St. Peter's Square in Rome. The Pope is rushed to the Agostino Gemelli University Polyclinic to undergo emergency surgery and survives.

entities.name: Attempted assassination of Pope John Paul II

events.description: Police bombed MOVE headquarters in Philadelphia, killing six adults and five children, and destroying the homes of 250 city residents.
events.html: • 1985 – Police bombed MOVE headquarters in Philadelphia, killing six adults and five children, and destroying the homes of 250 city residents.

events.description: Large groups of students occupy Tiananmen Square and begin a hunger strike.
events.html: • 1989 – Large groups of students occupy Tiananmen Square and begin a hunger strike.

events.description: The Dinamo–Red Star riot took place at Maksimir Stadium in Zagreb, Croatia between the Bad Blue Boys (fans of Dinamo Zagreb) and the Delije (fans of Red Star Belgrade).
events.html: • 1990 – The Dinamo–Red Star riot took place at Maksimir Stadium in Zagreb, Croatia between the Bad Blue Boys (fans of Dinamo Zagreb) and the Delije (fans of Red Star Belgrade).

events.description: Li Hongzhi gives the first public lecture on Falun Gong in Changchun, People's Republic of China.
events.html: • 1992 – Li Hongzhi gives the first public lecture on Falun Gong in Changchun, People's Republic of China.

events.description: Alison Hargreaves, a 33-year-old British mother, becomes the first woman to conquer Everest without oxygen or the help of sherpas.
events.html: • 1995 – Alison Hargreaves, a 33-year-old British mother, becomes the first woman to conquer Everest without oxygen or the help of sherpas.

events.description: Severe thunderstorms and a tornado in Bangladesh kill 600 people.
events.html: • 1996 – Severe thunderstorms and a tornado in Bangladesh kill 600 people.

events.description: Race riots break out in Jakarta, Indonesia, where shops owned by Indonesians of Chinese descent are looted and women raped.
events.html: • 1998 – Race riots break out in Jakarta, Indonesia, where shops owned by Indonesians of Chinese descent are looted and women raped.

events.description: India carries out two nuclear weapon tests at Pokhran, following the three conducted on May 11. The United States and Japan impose economic sanctions on India.
events.html: • 1998 – India carries out two nuclear weapon tests at Pokhran, following the three conducted on May 11. The United States and Japan impose economic sanctions on India.

events.description: A fireworks storage depot explodes in a residential neighborhood in Enschede, Netherlands, killing 23 people and injuring 950 others.
events.html: • 2000 – A fireworks storage depot explodes in a residential neighborhood in Enschede, Netherlands, killing 23 people and injuring 950 others.[14]

events.description: Andijan uprising, Uzbekistan; Troops open fire on crowds of protestors after a prison break; at least 187 people were killed according to official estimates.
events.html: • 2005 – Andijan uprising, Uzbekistan; Troops open fire on crowds of protestors after a prison break; at least 187 people were killed according to official estimates.

events.description: São Paulo violence: Rebellions occur in several prisons in Brazil.
events.html: • 2006 – São Paulo violence: Rebellions occur in several prisons in Brazil.

events.description: Two bombs explode in the Charsadda District of Pakistan killing 98 people and wounding 140 others.
events.html: • 2011 – Two bombs explode in the Charsadda District of Pakistan killing 98 people and wounding 140 others.

events.description: Forty-nine dismembered bodies are discovered by Mexican authorities on Mexican Federal Highway 40.
events.html: • 2012 – Forty-nine dismembered bodies are discovered by Mexican authorities on Mexican Federal Highway 40.

events.description: American physician Kermit Gosnell is found guilty in Pennsylvania of murdering three infants born alive during attempted abortions, involuntary manslaughter of a woman during an abortion procedure, and other charges.
events.html: • 2013 – American physician Kermit Gosnell is found guilty in Pennsylvania of murdering three infants born alive during attempted abortions, involuntary manslaughter of a woman during an abortion procedure, and other charges.[15]

events.description: An explosion at an underground coal mine in southwest Turkey kills 301 miners.
events.html: • 2014 – An explosion at an underground coal mine in southwest Turkey kills 301 miners.[16]
